title: Front Cover
content: Macro-vegetation benthic survey by diver Martina Jeuthe (Umeå Marine Sciences Centre, Sweden) of a Cladophora glomerata dominated assemblage along the Swedish Höga Kusten (High Coast) in the Gulf of Bothnia - a northern extension of the Baltic Sea and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Here, the brackish water enables both marine and freshwater species to co-exist, establishing unique aquatic communities with priority conservation status. Photo credit: Joakim Ahlgren
